Self Study Questions

1. If you were to describe semantic HTML to the next cohort of students, what would you say?

It's using tags that make it more clear what's going on in the code:  <p> instead of <span>, <header> instead of <div>, etc.  Using more decriptive tags to bring new clarity to the code

2. Name two big differences between display: block; and display: inline;.

* Inline lets you more easily manage child elements on the same line.


3. What are the 4 areas of the box model?

* Margins on the outside
 
* Borders on the outside

* Padding around the content and inside the borders

* Content


4. While using flexbox, what axis does the following property work on: align-items: center?


* Works on the cross axis.



5. Explain why git is valuable to a team of developers.

It's a way to keep your work local so that you don't add to the project until you're ready, and the versions and modifications are managable. 


